If I tell you "it's clear go ahead" and you build a product, invest money, launch it, and then someone sends a legal notice \'97 I would have done you real harm with false confidence.\
\

\f2\b What you actually need is this.
\f1\b0 \
In India specifically go to ipindia.gov.in. This is the official trademark registry. Search "Sugati" under class 36 which covers financial services and class 9 which covers software applications. These are your two relevant classes.\
This search itself is free and you can do it today in ten minutes.\
\

\f2\b Then one conversation with a trademark attorney.
\f1\b0 \
Not a big law firm. Just a practicing IP lawyer. In India a trademark search opinion costs somewhere between \uc0\u8377 2000 to \u8377 5000. That one conversation will give you legally defensible clarity. And if Sugati is clear, filing a trademark application in India is roughly \u8377 4500 per class.\
That is the cost of protecting everything you are about to build.\
