\f4\i \cf2 Why does digital money feel invisible?
\f1\i0 \
When we paid cash, we felt it. UPI changed everything \'97 and quietly took away that feeling. We spend without awareness. Not because we are careless. Because the feedback loop is broken.\
I called it\'a0
\f2\b Spend-na.
\f1\b0 \'a0"Spend" + "Na" \'97 like a mother saying\'a0
\f4\i na na beta
\f1\i0 \'a0before you do something you might regret.\
Not a budget app. Not a tracker. A mirror.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 Here is what happened next.
\f1\b0 \
I opened Claude. I typed my idea in plain English. No code. No technical specs. Just the philosophy, the feeling, the product I wanted to build.\
What followed was the most intense product session I have experienced in 15 years of IT.\
We debated bucket names. We threw away "wants" and "needs" because they felt judgmental. We landed on four buckets \'97 Necessary, Committed, Comfortable, Luxury \'97 each with a warm story behind it.\
We argued about tone. No guilt. Ever. Awareness, not judgment.\
We built screen by screen. Home. Sort. Picture. History. Limits. Education. Every design decision was a conversation \'97 not me instructing, not AI guessing, but both of us thinking together.\
By midnight,\'a0
\f2\b Spend-na was running on my iPhone.
\f1\b0 \
\

\f2\b What I learned about AI \'97 and about myself.
\f1\b0 \
AI did not build my app. I built my app. AI made it possible.\
The ideas were mine. The philosophy was mine. The name, the product decisions, the "no guilt" rule, the Yes/No question at month end \'97 all mine.\
AI handled what I could not \'97 the code, the architecture, the debugging. But every time AI suggested something that did not feel right, I pushed back. And it listened.\
That is the real lesson.\'a0
\f2\b AI amplifies the human who knows what they want.
\f1\b0 \
The founders, the product thinkers, the people with conviction and clarity \'97 they become 10x more powerful. The people waiting for AI to tell them what to build will still be waiting.\
\

\f2\b Spend-na is not on the App Store yet.
\f1\b0 \
But it exists. On my phone. With my hummingbird logo that I designed years ago \'97 not knowing it would one day be the face of a product I built in one night.\
The hummingbird dissolves into digital pixels. Money going invisible. Awareness bringing it back.\
If you are sitting on an idea \'97 start the conversation. You might surprise yourself.\
